results.name: Number of ways to partition n labeled elements into pie slices of different odd sizes, allowing the pie to be turned over.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200
program: (PARI) seq(n)=[subst(serlaplace(p/y + polcoeff(p,1) + polcoeff(p,2)),y,1)/2 | p <- Vec(serlaplace(y-1+prod(k=1, ceil(n/2), 1 + x^(2*k-1)*y/(2*k-1)! + O(x*x^n))))] \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Sep 11 2018
results.author: _Christian G. Bower_
